===Etymology===
From Anglo-Norman ''[[autour]]'', from Old French ''[[autor]]'', from Latin ''[[auctor]]'', from ''[[augere]]'' “to increase”, “to originate”

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|[[RP]] /ˈɔːθə/}}
*{{audio|en-us-author.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔːθə(r)|-ɔːθə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# The [[originator]] or [[creator]] of a [[work]], especially a [[literary]] [[composition]]; a [[writer]].
# [[Source]] of information.

